          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>Single folio; Writing surface: paper (dyed pink); Shelfmark: 2007.120; Qurʾānic Text: Q 61:14-62:1, Q 82:1-82:8; 5 lines per page; Dimensions: 254 x 330mm;  Script style: Maġribī <hi rend="italic">mabsūṭ </hi>(for the <hi rend="italic">rasm</hi>); Estimated date of production: Shortly before 650/1252; Provenance: Marrakesh. </p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>  </p>
              <p>These are 2 folios from the tenth volume of a Qurʾān originally in ten volumes, endowed by the penultimate Almohad caliph al-Murtaḍā to the tomb of one of his wives, in 650/1252. Eight of the original ten volumes are still kept in Marrakesh, Ibn Yūsuf Library, ms. 431. Another monumental Almohad Qurʾān, probably copied by the same calligrapher in the exact same style of Maġribī <hi rend="italic">mabsūṭ </hi>script, is in the Topkapı Palace Library, ms. R. 21–24.</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>This  is a collection of the fragments under the shelfmark 2007.120, consisting  of <ref target="https://dia.org/collection/folio-ten-volume-qur-96583">2007.120.1A</ref> and <ref target="https://dia.org/collection/folio-ten-volume-qur-96584">1B</ref>, as well as <ref target="https://dia.org/collection/folio-ten-volume-qur-97711">2007.120.2A</ref> and <ref target="https://dia.org/collection/folio-ten-volume-qur-97712">2B</ref>. For further information about the fragments in question, also see the linked pages of the Detroit Institute of Arts.</p>
              <p> </p>
            </summary>
